%% Diagram: Store-and-Forward Message Flow
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor Sender
    participant SConn as Sender's chat node
    participant Router as Routing layer (pg2/wandist)
    participant RConn as Recipient's chat node
    participant Mnesia as Offline queue (Mnesia)
    actor Recipient

    Sender->>SConn: send(msg)
    SConn->>Router: lookup(recipient)

    alt Recipient online, same cluster
        Router->>RConn: forward(msg) [sub-ms]
        RConn->>Recipient: deliver
        Recipient-->>RConn: ack
        RConn-->>SConn: delivered
    else Recipient online, different cluster
        Router->>RConn: forward via wandist [sub-second]
        RConn->>Recipient: deliver
        Recipient-->>RConn: ack
        RConn-->>SConn: delivered
    else Recipient offline
        Router->>Mnesia: enqueue(msg) + replicate to peer
        Mnesia-->>SConn: queued
        Note over Recipient,RConn: Up to 30 day TTL
        Recipient->>RConn: reconnect
        RConn->>Mnesia: drain queue (ordered)
        Mnesia->>RConn: msgs
        RConn->>Recipient: deliver
        Recipient-->>RConn: ack
    end

    RConn->>Mnesia: delete on ack
    Note over Mnesia: Server is a router,\nnot an archive
